data.title: Great Food & Karaoke
data.text:
We didn't actually dine inside the restaurant, but ordered food to go. While the kitchen prepared our food, my husband was offered water or something else to drink and enjoyed some great karaoke - in Spanish!!!! He called me on the phone and held it up so I could hear the great singing in the background. Per his observation, the place was busy but service was great and the establishment kept very clean. Now about the food: The chips and pico de gallo are freshly prepared and tasty. My taco salad was huge and delicious. It is very healthy for a taco salad, so if you want cheese or sour cream, you need to request it (I didn't). While rice traditionally tends to be a bit soggy in this entree, this rice was moist but firm, and delicious. My husband had a carne asade burrito that took him two days to eat!
The next time we are in town, we will definitely dine in, and, after some liquid encouragement, may even sing a song or two.
